<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 727/70 1 of 21 April 1970 on the common organisation of the market in raw tobacco, and in particular Article 9 (4) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 727/70 toortubakaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 9 l&otilde;iget 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas international trade in raw tobacco is concerned only with baled tobacco, the only form in which it may be stored in technically satisfactory conditions; whereas, therefore, the granting of export refunds on raw tobacco should be limited to baled tobacco produced from leaf tobacco harvested in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: toortubaka rahvusvaheline kaubandus k&auml;sitleb ainult pallpakendis tubakat, ainsat vormi, milles on v&otilde;imalik s&auml;ilitada tubakat tehniliselt rahuldavates tingimustes; seep&auml;rast tuleks toortubaka jaoks eksporditoetuse andmist piirata &uuml;henduses koristatud lehttubakast toodetud pallpakendis tubakaga; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas price and marketing conditions vary according to the varieties of tobacco harvested in the Community; whereas it is therefore necessary to fix the refund at different amounts for each variety; </inglise>
<eesti> hind ja turutingimused varieeruvad vastavalt &uuml;henduses koristatud tubakasortidele; seep&auml;rast on vaja iga sordi jaoks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata erinevad toetuse m&auml;&auml;rad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the baled tobacco produced from leaf tobacco of a particular harvest may be marketed over a relatively lengthy period; whereas certain of the factors on which the criteria for fixing the refund are based may vary according to the year in which the tobacco is produced; whereas, therefore, provision should be made to vary the refund on a particular variety of tobacco according to the crop year; </inglise>
<eesti> eri saakide lehttubakast toodetud pallpakendis tubakat v&otilde;ib turustada suhteliselt pika ajavahemiku jooksul; teatavad tegurid, millele toetuse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise kriteeriumid tuginevad, v&otilde;ivad varieeruda vastavalt tubaka tootmise aastale; seep&auml;rast tuleks s&auml;testada eri tubakasortide toetuse varieerimine vastavalt viljelusaastale; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the refunds must be fixed in accordance with certain criteria which enable the difference to be covered between the prices of baled tobacco produced in the Community for which a premium has been granted and world prices; whereas, moreover, account should also be taken, for each variety, of the conditions under which the produce is disposed of commercially in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> toetused tuleb kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata vastavalt teatavatele kriteeriumidele, mis v&otilde;imaldavad katta erinevuse &uuml;henduses toodetud, lisatasu saanud pallpakendis tubaka hindade ja maailmaturuhindade vahel; lisaks sellele tuleks iga sordi puhul arvesse v&otilde;tta tingimused, mille alusel toodang &uuml;henduses realiseeritakse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to determine the amount it is also necessary to take into consideration market preparation, transport and shipment costs incurred; </inglise>
<eesti> summa kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseks on samuti vaja arvesse v&otilde;tta turundus- ja veokulusid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision should be made for varying the amount of the refund according to the destination of the products to take account of the varying distances of markets from the Community market and of the special conditions applying to imports in certain countries of destination; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada toetuse m&auml;&auml;ra varieerimine vastavalt toodete sihtkohale, et v&otilde;tta arvesse turgude erinevad kaugused &uuml;henduse turust ja sisseveo suhtes kohaldatavad eritingimused teatavates sihtriikides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the factors to be taken into account in applying Article 9 (1) second subparagraph of Regulation (EEC) No 727/70, should be determined; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata tegurid, mis v&otilde;etakse arvesse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 727/70 artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 1 teise l&otilde;igu kohaldamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, to avoid distortions of competition, the trade should be subject to the same administrative conditions throughout the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> konkurentsi moonutamise v&auml;ltimiseks tuleks kogu &uuml;henduse kaubanduses kohaldada samu haldustingimusi, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The granting of export refunds on raw tobacco shall be limited to baled tobacco produced from leaf tobacco harvested in the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> Eksporditoetuste andmist toortubaka jaoks piiratakse &uuml;henduses koristatud lehttubakast toodetud pallpakendis tubakaga. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The refunds shall be determined for each variety produced in the Community in the light of the following factors: </inglise>
<eesti> Toetused m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks iga &uuml;henduses kasvatatud sordi jaoks, pidades silmas j&auml;rgmiseid tegureid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the situation and trend: </inglise>
<eesti> a) olukord ja arengusuund: </eesti>
<inglise> - of prices, supply and demand in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> - hinnad, tarnimine ja n&otilde;udlus &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> - of world prices; </inglise>
<eesti> - maailmaturuhinnad; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the lowest market preparation and transport costs within the Community and the lowest shipment costs to the country of destination; </inglise>
<eesti> b) k&otilde;ige madalamad turundus- ja veokulud &uuml;henduses ja k&otilde;ige madalamad sihtriiki vedamise kulud; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the economic aspect of the proposed exports. </inglise>
<eesti> c) kavandatava v&auml;ljaveo majanduslik aspekt. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The refund may vary for tobacco of a given variety according to the crop Year. </inglise>
<eesti> Samale tubakasordile antav toetus v&otilde;ib olla erinev vastavalt viljelusaastale. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> When the world market situation or the special requirements of certain markets make it necessary, the Community refund for one or more varieties may vary according to their destination. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui maailmaturu olukorda v&otilde;i teatavate turgude erin&otilde;udeid silmas pidades osutub vajalikuks, v&otilde;ib &uuml;henduse toetust &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme sordi puhul muuta vastavalt nende sihtkohale. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> In order to assess the exceptional cases referred to in the second subparagraph of Article 9 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 727/70, account shall be taken in particular of the special conditions existing for certain export markets, such as exceptionally high transport costs or the special characteristics of these markets. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 727/70 artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 1 teises l&otilde;igus osutatud erandjuhtude hindamiseks v&otilde;etakse arvesse eelk&otilde;ige teatavate eksporditurgude eritingimused, n&auml;iteks erandlikult k&otilde;rged veokulud v&otilde;i nende turgude erijooned. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The refund shall be paid upon proof that the products: </inglise>
<eesti> Toetuse saamiseks t&otilde;endatakse, et toode: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) have been grown in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> a) on kasvatatud &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) have come from the crop for which the refund is requested; </inglise>
<eesti> b) on p&auml;rit saagist, mille jaoks on toetust taotletud; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) have been exported from the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> c) on &uuml;hendusest v&auml;lja veetud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where Article 3 applies, the refund shall be paid under the conditions laid down in paragraph 1 provided it is shown that the product has reached the destination for which the refund was fixed. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kohaldatakse artiklit 3, makstakse toetust vastavalt l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tingimustele, eeldusel et toode on saabunud sihtkohta, mille jaoks on toetus kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud. </eesti>
<inglise> However, exceptions may be made to this rule in accordance with the procedure referred to in paragraph 3, provided conditions are laid down offering equivalent guarantees. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellest reeglist v&otilde;idakse siiski teha erandeid artiklis 3 osutatud korras, kui on s&auml;testatud tingimused, mis pakuvad samav&auml;&auml;rseid tagatisi. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Additional provisions, in particular for regulating the granting of refunds, may be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 17 of Regulation (EEC) No 727/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisas&auml;tteid, eriti toetuste andmise kontrollimist reguleerivaid &uuml;ksikasjalikke s&auml;tteid v&otilde;ib vastu v&otilde;tta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 727/70 artikliga 17 etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
